The paper proposes a new reinforcement learning algorithm that addresses value estimation errors by using a state-action return distribution function. This is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning, specifically reinforcement learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with continuous control tasks, which suggests that it may also fall under cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also proposes a new architecture to improve learning efficiency, which suggests that it may also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
